body:
## Steps to Reproduce

1. Go to Android Studio preferences
2. Search for "widget"

This doesn't find the `Run applications with --track-widget-creation` checkbox.

![intellij_preferences_bug mp4](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/919717/40865304-7db93344-65ac-11e8-94c7-5d49ba9b4bfb.gif)

This is the case for all options for the Flutter (and I think even the Dart) plugin — not just the option shown above. 

It's interesting that when I'm on that page and I start typing "widget", it'll highlight the option for a while, but then it will auto-update the list of relevant pages on the left panel, and it won't have that page there.

## Version info

comment_data.body: Generally the bug is to make sure all our options show up in the quick search not just that this specific one does.
@alexander-doroshko I noticed the Dart plugin settings are also not searchable. Any idea how to fix it?

Dart plugin settings are probably not searchable in Android Studio and IntelliJ IDEA Community Edition but searchable in Ultimate Edition and WebStorm. I don't know exact steps to fix it at the moment. I think we need to debug the logic in IntelliJ Platform that searches for the settings. The fix might require changes in the Platform. We have a similar issue on our issue tracker: https://youtrack.jetbrains.com/issue/WEB-35257
Since this is a platform issue, I'm closing this.

@stevemessick @jacob314 I've found `SearchableOptionContributor` extension point in IntelliJ Platform that seems to allow fixing this on the plugin end. Here's how I made 'dart closing labels' and some other options searchable: https://github.com/JetBrains/intellij-plugins/commit/4c64def4de519fa8507564b54e664e2395fcb859 and https://github.com/JetBrains/intellij-plugins/commit/20b41b03a514b286b5db933d186fd5ad286eb80a
